        "subject": "LU-10927 osc: do not spend too much time in osc_lru_reclaim",
        "message": "LU-10927 osc: do not spend too much time in osc_lru_reclaim\n\nWhen a IO calls osc_lru_reclaim(), it needs the LRU slots immediately.\nSo if the thread is asking for less than max_pages_per_rpc slots,\ndo not waste time to shrink max_pages_per_rpc slots. The overhead\nwill become much more significant when memory gets bigger.\n\nSigned-off-by: Li Xi <lixi@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: Ia9a5f7756f931db8bcb0a23d14914712fa804004\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
